line_1: "O'er well-rang'd hives the bees shall swarm,
Beaux without number, daily round her swarm,
line_2: And each with fulsome flatt'ry try's to charm.

line_1: And when so many choice Productions swarm,
line_2: Must only Satire keep your Fancies warm?

line_1: Or gild the surge with infect-sparks, that swarm
line_2: Round the bright oar, the kindling prow alarm;

line_1: That in each guinea conqu'ring Cupids swarm,
line_2: And Venus less than good King George can charm?
